The headline print in quarterly GDP missed the mark even as consumer spending, the biggest component of U.S. economic activity, exceeded expectations. Personal consumption rose at an 11.8% rate in the second quarter, unexpectedly accelerating from the first quarter's 11.4% growth rate and handily topping expectations for a 10.5% increase.
